flowRoot.flowPara: Edit the page title and other page settings here
Edit the page content using the Visual Editor (Elementor). Images, text, galleries, etc..
Change the sidebar style and widget area for this page.
Change the footer widget area and visibility for the current pgae
To change the menu items go to Appearance > Menu
Click this to access your backend WordPress dashboard from any page of the website.
The header image can be set from Appearance > Customize > Header Image.
Access the theme Customizer. Change fonts, colors and other default settings.
Logout of WordPress or access your profile
This is an "Image Carousel". Click "Edit with Elementor" to edit the images and settings for this element.
This is a "text block". Click "Edit with Elementor" to edit this text. See advanced tab for borders.
The contents of this widget come from a page called "About Sidebar". Edit this page in Elementor.
You can insert latest blog posts onto any page using Elementor. This is set to show the two latest.
This is the blog featured image. Edit a blog post and change the image from the bottom right.
Make sure "Excerpt" is enabled when editing a blog post (see Screen Options"). This lets you set a custom excerpt instead of the auto generated one.
Go to Appearance > Widgets and change the Instagram settings to match your username
These are normal sidebar widgets. To change go to Appearance > Widgets
These are changed from Appearance > Widgets. Drag your widgets into the "Footer" area.
Change the Footer Text from Appearance > Customize > Site Identity
The logo can be changed from Appearance > Customize > Site Identity
The grunge style can be removed in Customizer or on individual blog post pages.
This shows how many comments a blog post has. Share will open up some post sharing options.
Go to Appearance > Customize > Fonts to change all the different font styles.
Go to "Contact" > "Contact Forms" > "Footer Signup" to change this contact form settings.
